{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C and grease a large loaf tin (900 g) with oil then set aside.","Place rice in mixing bowl and grind <nobr>2 min\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place dates and apples in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>.","Add oil, reserved ground rice, baking powder, bicarbonate of soda, xantham gum, salt, sugar, walnuts, eggs and water then mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Transfer to prepared tin and bake for approx. 50 minutes (180°C) or until a skewer inserted in the centre comes out clean. Remove loaf from tin and allow to cool on a wire rack.  Slice before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["60 g olive oil, plus extra for greasing","240 g brown rice","80 g pitted dates","140 g apples, quartered","1 ½ tsp gluten free baking powder","1 tsp bicarbonate of soda","½ tsp xantham gum","½ tsp fine sea salt","60 g sugar","80 g walnut pieces","3 large eggs","100 g water"]}],"id":"r82315","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-IrNWISSYHDU\/XZWrwKW-9nI\/AAAAAAAAfsQ\/tuxZQayVHOk8cDLlvaMww0IORIHdaGczACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ts7r-97ARexaAJkk.png","title":"Gluten-Free Date, Apple and Walnut Tea Bread","publishedAt":"2015-05-13T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3.2 g","fat":"8.8 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"20.7 g","calories":"731 kJ \/ 175 kcal"},"usefulItems":"900 g loaf tin (2 lb), cooling rack, skewer, oven","hintsAndTricks":["The walnuts can be substituted for almonds; chop with dates and apple in step 3."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","1h","16 slices"]}